title: Tootie's April 2014 Mix
description:
Skrillex, Juicy J, Steel Panther and Chicago on the same mix... typical Tootie. This may be the last Tootie mix of its kind to be constrained to a CD-R time limit. This mix features co-production from Albert Avery Harrington.

    Skrillex - First of the Year (Equinox) (Tootie Edit)
    Kid Ink ft. Chris Brown - Show Me
    Ludacris ft. Mystikal & I-20 - Move Bitch
    Juicy J ft. Lil Wayne & 2 Chainz - Bandz a Make Her Dance*
    Yung Joc ft. Nitti - It's Goin Down*
    N*E*R*D ft. Lee Harvey & Vita - Lapdance
    Flo Rida ft. T-Pain - Low
    Pitbull ft. Ke$ha - Timber
    Robert Palmer - Hyperactive
    Lynyrd Skynyrd - Free Bird
    Korn - A.D.I.D.A.S.
    Steel Panther - Party Like Tomorrow is the End of the World
    Loverboy - Turn Me Loose
    Men at Work - Down Under
    Rick Springfield - Jessie's Girl
    Puddle of Mudd - Blurry
    Meat Loaf ft. Lorraine Crosby - I'd Do Anything for Love
    Chicago - Look Away

*The instrumental appears to be at least partially lossily-sourced

All tracks are sourced from lossless material. All of the compilations' songs utilize playback gain values from Tootie's personal volume-leveling procedure, resulting in a consistent overall listening experience without the need to adjust the volume between songs. The method focuses on vocal volume.

Details:
Format: FLAC, level 7
Length: 1:23:22.0911
Average bitrate: 866 kbps
Embedded CUE Sheet

Playback verified with foobar2000.


Notes:
Produced to be overburned to an 80-minute CD-R.
The use of the tracks in the compilation independently is not recommended as most tracks are intermixed in some way. Some are shortened.
